    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="910"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d910">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00114A Pacific War/396: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-07">April 7,
                            1943</date>.<lb/>[Received April 7—8:43 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2179. American interests Far East. Department’s 2868, December 19.<note n="15"
                        xml:id="d910fn15">
                        <ref target="frus1942v01#pg_839">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1942, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 839</ref>.</note> Legation’s 6222,
                    December 30.<note n="16" xml:id="d910fn16">Not printed, but see footnote 98,
                            <ref target="#pg_1013">p. 1013</ref>.</note> Swiss Legation Tokyo
                    telegraphs following reply from Japanese Government: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“In principle Japanese Government not opposed sending correspondence and
                            packages to American prisoners of war, civilian internees Japan and
                            territories under Japanese control but cannot authorize neutral ships
                            enter waters where military operation taking place.</p>
                        <p>However, if American Government disposed send Vladivostok correspondence
                            and packages for American internees either by Soviet <pb facs="1032"
                                n="1020" xml:id="pg_1020"/> ship or by land across Siberia Japanese
                            Government ready examine possibility relieving present situation.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
